    • Method Detail

      • inject

        public void inject(@NotNull
                   java.lang.reflect.Field field,
                   @NotNull
                   java.lang.Object fixture,
                   @NotNull
                   java.lang.String value)

        Injects the given field of the given fixture instance with the given String value.

        Before injecting the field, the String value will be converted into an object of the appropriate type. This is done by looking up a matching interface TypeConverter as follows:

        1. field

        2. class

        3. document

        4. default

        This method is capable of injecting any field of the given fixture instance. If the field is not public, it will be made so.

        Parameters:
        field - the Field to inject
        fixture - the fixture instance to invoke the method on
        value - the value for the injected field as strings
        Throws:
        FixtureFieldInjectionException - in case anything went wrong with the injection
        See Also:
        String, String, interface TypeConverter
